    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with **Gunnar Henderson** and **Jacob Wilson** headlining our offensive attack. **Gunnar Henderson** (78.99) is our clear top play; despite a moderate matchup against Lambert, his leadoff spot, combined with a significant 16% park factor boost and his ability to maximize platoon splits against right-handed pitching, makes him the engine of today\u2019s production. Similarly, **Jacob Wilson** (71.63) provides elite value at the top of the order, benefiting from a favorable 10% park factor and a manageable matchup against Cameron. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (67.95) remains a strong play, we are monitoring his lineup status closely; should he shift out of the #3 hole, that efficiency score will fluctuate, though his recent xwOBA metrics suggest he is due for a productive outing against Ober.\n\nWe are navigating a tricky middle-infield situation today, as **Nasim Nunez** (45.93) occupies a slot primarily for his disruptive potential on the basepaths. While his raw projections are marginal, his 4% efficiency boost against a slow-delivery pitcher underscores our strategy to chase stolen bases\u2014a category where **Nasim Nunez** provides essential volume. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (59.83) rounds out our middle infield as a high-floor option, buoyed by a 14% platoon advantage against Peralta. Conversely, the bench decision was tight between **Coby Mayo** (43.05) and our deeper reserves. **Coby Mayo** retained his spot despite a mediocre score because the park factors in his venue are too lucrative to ignore, even against a tough arm like Lambert. Our top-tier assets like **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Jackson Merrill**, and **Andy Pages** are unavailable today due to schedule conflicts or injury, placing the onus on **Drake Baldwin** (53.50) and **Heliot Ramos** (46.99) to stabilize the floor while we wait for reinforcements like **Jordan Westburg**, **Jorge Polanco**, and **Josh Lowe** to cycle back into active roles.",
